args: Delphi has resolved to perform a forbidden\nritual that will banish his inherited power\nfrom the world for good.

But in order to perform the ritual, he needs
the cooperation of a royal family member.
Thus, he sets out on a journey to find
just such a person...
I thought Emile might be persuaded\nto aid me, but it was a fool's errand.
But giving up? Not an option.\nI yet need someone to... Hmm?
Well, lookit what we got 'ere, boys!\nThis one smells proper rich, so 'e do.
What say ya spare a few coppers\nfor us poor starvin' lads, friend?
That's clearly a threat dressed up as a\nrequest. You really should reconsider\nsome of your life choices.
Oy! I'll show ya what 'appens to folks what\nquestion me life choices!
That's the youngest prince of Alberia!
I know not his purpose in this place,\nbut it works to my great advantage.\nI must ensure he wins the day!
Stay back, Your Highness!\nThese rabble are mine!
Perhaps not the greatest time for the\nsharing of pleasantries? No. Not at all.\nNow pray stand aside as I work.
I call forth the power of the Tutelary!\nRestrain these villains! Purgatorial Cage!
Wow. That was just...wow.\nWho ARE you?
Uh oh. He's passed out. And he's running a\nfever. I need to get him back to Cleo.
Glad to see you up and around.\nOh, and you're in our castle.
I brought you here after you collapsed.
Apologies. Many of them, and most keen.\nI meant no burden to you.
I'm happy to help. But if you feel up to it,\ncould you tell me a bit about yourself?\nYou seemed to recognize me earlier.
My name is Delphi, and I am a member\nof the Tutelary tribe. We guard the ruins\nwhere the Shards sleep.

Some 300 years ago, King Alberius
charged us with creating and maintaining
seals on the Binding Ruins. This we did
unfailingly, until the recent past.
That's right, now I remember.\nEr, but what happened recently?
The seals? Broken. The Shards? Purloined.\nThus have I left the ruins and come in\nsearch of a royal family member.
As our tribe now lacks a purpose, I seek\nto use my power to conduct a final ritual.
But said ritual? It requires the cooperation\nof a royal family member.
Our power is sworn to the Alberian royal\nfamily; thus do we require your consent.
This boon. Will you grant it?
It sounds like our family owes\na great deal to you and your kin.
Repaying that service is the least I can do.

There's also the little matter of you saving
my own life back there with those bandits.
Anyway, you're welcome to stay here and
prepare for the ritual as long as you need.
You must let me aid you in return.

Well, if you're dead-set on pitching in
around here, you could use that power
you demonstrated. Frankly, I've never
seen anything like it.
You speak of the power of the Tutelary\ntribe. This emblem? On my forehead?\nIt permits the wielding of that power.
So the emblem is a blessing of sorts?\nThat's quite fascinating.
Apologiesmy mouth ran where it\nshould have come to heel.
Er, okay? Anyway, it should be nice to\nhave you around. I'm guessing we're\npretty much the same age, right?
I am ten years your senior, at least.
Wait, really? I had no idea.\nYou look so...um...
Boyish? Youthful? Green? I am not.\nThe power gives all who wield it\nthe mien of a younger self.
This power has been mine for as long as I\nhave been me, such that my chronology\nand appearance are increasingly at odds.
Huh. Okay then. Well, maybe it'll be\nmore of an older-brother thing, then.
Well, an older-brother figure, at least.\nHonestly, there are a lot of folks here\nwho I think of in that kind of way.
Anyway, now that you're going to be one\nof us, I should introduce you to everybody.\nHang onI'll be right back.
*sigh* I've no right to be called\na brother by him.
But his dragonblood? Essential.\nSo I will do as I must!
